  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Yemen RC DM strengthening Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective: To strengthen the Disaster Management capacity of YRCS at the headquarters and branch level (four targeted branches) and simultaneously build the capacity of at-risk communities to be prepared for and able to respond to disasters. Outcome 1: YRCS has improved institutional Disaster Management (DM) capacities at national and branch levels as per Movement and sector standards Outcome 2: First aid services are available in target communities and schools Outcome 3: At-risk communities are aware of and taken action for disaster preparedness and response measures for resilience This programme is jointly funded by the British Red Cross and Swedish Red Cross (division of funding is clarified in log frame and budget). SRC and BRC supported DM capacity development of YRCS through the IFRC during 2017. A DM Capacity Assessment using the Well-Prepared National Society (WPNS) tool and exercise was carried out and based on the findings and recommendations of this the IFRC developed a Plan of Action (PoA) to set clear priorities and monitor progress moving forward. The YRCS DM CB programme started in April 2018 and a midterm review was conducted in June-July 2019. This led to a Re-Design and Learning Workshop held in Djibouti in August 2019 in which all stakeholders were present and engaged in the plans for the remainder of the programme. The result led to a revised PoA and budget agreed to by all partners to continue the programme until December 2019. Full details are provided in Annex 2: Project Proposal - YRCS DMCB Re-design and Learning Workshop Report. During this period IFRC will continue to support YRCS to complete the activities planned in the revised PoA to build and strengthen YRCS DM capacity. The project will have two approaches. The first is to build the capacity of headquarters and the four targeted branches Amran Dhamar Shabwa and Al Mahra; these branches are selected based on the vulnerability and type of hazard/disaster such as cyclone flood earthquake and forced displacement by conflict. The second is to address and build the capacity of the communities. The PoA is divided into three outcomes to achieve a holistic approach to enhance the DM capacity within the YRCS (HQ and branch level) and within at-risk communities as well as strengthening resilience measures within the communities.</narrative>
  </description>
